.TH "SIMPLE_SHELL" "1" "03 aout, 2022" "simple_shell 1.0.0" "User Manual"
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
simple_shell \- rebuilt version of the standard command language
interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
We\[cq]ve recreated a basic shell with few options, prompt will appears
and wait for a command.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Executes commands read from the standard input or from a file.
.SH Overview
.PP
This shell will read line from the STDIN_FILENO
.SH LEXICAL STRUCTURE
.PP
The shell reads input in terms of lines from a file and breaks it up
into words at whitespace (blanks and tabs), and at certain sequences of
characters that are special to the shell called \[lq]operators\[rq].
.SH INVOCATION
.PP
Can be executed either in Interactive or Non\-interactive
.SS Interactive Mode
.PP
Read and execute lines until an EOF is sent on an empty line.
.SS Non\-interactive mode
.PP
If the shell is executed in a pipe, it will read and execute any
commands received then stop.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Non\-Interactive Mode
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
$ echo \[dq]ls *.c\[dq] | ./hsh

    README.md get_args.c man_1_simple_shell simple_shell.c
\f[R]
.fi
.SS Interactive Mode
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
$ ./hsh

ls
    README.md get_args.c man_1_simple_shell simple_shell.c
\f[R]
.fi
.SH BUILT\-IN
.PP
exit \- Exit simple_shell
